{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-tsx","path":"/posts/how-to-clean-local-git-branches/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>Edit</h2>\n<p>Now, I use the script</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ <span class=\"token function\">cat</span> <span class=\"token variable\"><span class=\"token variable\">$(</span><span class=\"token function\">which</span> git-branchclean<span class=\"token variable\">)</span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">#!/usr/bin/env bash</span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">EDITOR</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token variable\">${EDITOR<span class=\"token operator\">:-</span>'code --wait'}</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> branch <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-v</span> <span class=\"token operator\">></span> /tmp/merged.txt <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$EDITOR</span> /tmp/merged.txt <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"token function\">cat</span> /tmp/merged.txt <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">awk</span> <span class=\"token string\">'{{ print $1 }}'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">|</span> <span class=\"token function\">xargs</span> <span class=\"token function\">git</span> branch <span class=\"token parameter variable\">-D</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Then, you can use</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> branchclean</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Original</h2>\n<p>After working on some projects, my github repository ended up having many branches locally because PR is usually merged in GitHub.</p>\n<p>To clean up old branches, I run the following.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre c